23/12/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said Monday (22 December) that the country is entering the most critical period in its efforts to join the EU. In a speech to parliament, Gul said efforts made over the past year should bear fruit next year. The government hopes negotiations on full EU membership will begin by the end of 2004.
In other news, Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan plans an official visit to Washington at the end of January, including a meeting with US counterpart George W. Bush. Aides say the two leaders will discuss bilateral relations and regional issues, including the dispute in Cyprus and the situation in Iraq. (Hurriyet - 23/12/03; Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, NTV - 22/12/03)
